ombined solutions” was good enough to convince their longsuffering owners led by private equity firm goldman sachs to recapitalize the brand in  that means put in more money they would ultimately hold del taco for  long years and murphy gives them credit “they were willing to give us the time and money to execute the strategy” he says it was also enough to attract the attention of larry levy the chicago restaurant tycoon who spent several months visiting del taco restaurants and putting together investors ultimately winning the unit del taco last june via a spac that stands for special purchase acquisition company which is a littleused vehicle these days “you see the spac’s are targeting businesses that are built out not purely speculative” like in the past murphy says “it was a perfect match” the deal came in two steps first the levy family and investors bought  million of del taco common stock  percent of the company and increased senior debt by  million under the existing credit agreement with ge capital those proceeds were used to retire  million in senior debt in step two a levy acquisition subsidiary merged into del taco taking the company public for a  million valuation to read the complete article click here atlanta – nrd capital management “nrd” via its initial investment fund nrd capital partners i lp announced its first acquisition with the purchase of frisch’s restaurants a unit cincinnatibased brand for approximately  million nrd capital partners is the first franchiseesponsored and managed investment fund focused on investing in  and accelerating the growth of – brands that offer superior products and compelling unit economics this is the right transaction for the company said retiring frisch’s ceo craig maier frisch’s has been a family operated business since my grandfather opened our first drivein in  on behalf of my entire family i’d like to thank our loyal customers for allowing us to serve them ever since with its first acquisition complete nrd’s 